<b>Susan Dumais</b> is a Principal Researcher in the Adaptive Systems &amp; Interaction Group of <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<military_unit wordnetid="108198398" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<division wordnetid="108213205" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<scientist wordnetid="110560637" confidence="0.8">
<army_unit wordnetid="108190754" confidence="0.8">
<research_worker wordnetid="110523076" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../522/2163522.xml">
Microsoft Research</link></research_worker>
</army_unit>
</scientist>
</causal_agent>
</division>
</person>
</military_unit>
</physical_entity>
.<p>

Before joining Microsoft in 1997, Dumais was a researcher at Bellcore (now <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../972/1141972.xml">
Telcordia Technologies</link></company>
), where she and her colleagues conducted research into what is now called the <link>
vocabulary problem</link> in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../271/15271.xml">
information retrieval</link>.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> Their study demonstrated, through a variety of experiments, that different people use different vocabulary to describe the same thing, and that even choosing the "best" term to describe something is not enough for others to find it.  One implication of this work is that because the author of a document may use different vocabulary than someone searching for the document, traditional <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../271/15271.xml">
information retrieval</link> methods will have limited success.</p>
<p>

Dumais and the other Bellcore researchers then began investigating ways to build search systems that avoided the vocabulary problem.  The result was their invention of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../427/689427.xml">
Latent Semantic Indexing</link>.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref></p>

<p>

In <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../164/36164.xml">
2006</link>, Dumais was inducted as a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../889/381889.xml">
Fellow</link> of the <organization wordnetid="108008335" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../ury/30th_century.xml">
Association for Computing Machinery</link></organization>
.</p>

